<p class="">The hon. Member is going to get it all. The right hon. Gentleman said: <blockquote><q>"What a thing to see the roads of this country covered with the volunteer youth of the nation drilling for a year with nothing but broomsticks and wooden muskets"—</q></blockquote> that was in the early stages of the first war— <blockquote><q>"and what a much more terrible thing to see those who were in the fighting line, in the trenches, under a continuous bombardment with batteries behind them that were limited to firing one round per battery per day."<span id="vol309_col2011" class="cross-reference" data-house-id="1" data-column-number="2011" data-volume-number="309">—[OFFICIAL REPORT, 10th March, 1936; Vol. 309, c. 2011.]</span></q></blockquote></p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
